2026-07-14 09:21:39,240 INFO freight_fate.transcript: Dispatch board. Dispatch assigns your load and route while you are a new company hire; load choice opens at level 8. Listed amounts are carrier gross; your settlement pays driver wages. Career objective: First-week service record. You can decline 3 more assigned loads before your next promotion, but refusals cost standing with dispatch. Market watch: food tight, general tight, retail loose, steel loose. Accept assigned dispatch: 14 tons of shipping containers from Phoenix Cross-Dock in Phoenix, Arizona to Buckeye Cross-Dock in Buckeye, Arizona. 40 miles. Carrier gross 836 dollars. Deadline 2 hours. Equipment: dry van trailer, or flatbed trailer. Carrier trailer provided. Estimated driver pay before advances: 297 dollars. Lane note: Market is tight. 1 of 3.
